\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy defines the structure and authority through which Information Technology (IT) governance is established,
 maintained,
 and executed within Elko County.
 It articulates the formal relationships,
 decision rights,
 and operational responsibilities required to ensure effective oversight,
 strategic alignment,
 and accountability for Information Operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County departments,
 elected officials,
 appointed leadership,
 and employees who interact with,
 procure,
 or rely on Information Operations services.
 It governs the mechanisms by which IT decisions are made,
 funded,
 and overseen.
\end_layout

