6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Delegated Governance Framework
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County hereby establishes a delegated governance model for IT oversight.
 While strategic direction and budget appropriation are established by the Board of County Commissioners,
 the execution of technical strategy is delegated to the Information Operations Department in accordance with the decision rights defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Program Leadership (NIST PM-2)
\series default
:
 The IT Director serves as the designated senior official with responsibility and authority to coordinate,
 develop,
 implement,
 and maintain the County's information security program,
 consistent with NIST SP 800-53 PM-2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Central Authority
\series default
:
 The Information Operations Department is designated as the sole authoritative source for all IT-related governance policy,
 technical standards,
 and architecture coordination across County departments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Operational Independence
\series default
:
 To ensure security and stability,
 the Information Operations Department shall operate with the autonomy required to enforce compliance standards,
 as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Policy and Enforcement Authority
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director holds the delegated authority to develop IT policy,
 enforce technical standards,
 and manage operational decisions.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Binding Nature
\series default
:
 The Information Operations Department shall enforce all formally adopted IT policies and technical standards across all Elko County departments,
 systems,
 and personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Management Control
\series default
:
 Consistent with 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy Section 5.1.1.4
\series default
 and applicable Management Control Agreements,
 the Criminal Justice Agency (CJA) retains management control over criminal justice functions and CJI.
 Within that framework,
 the IT Director (or designated CJIS Information Security Officer),
 acting as the CJA’s technical agent,
 shall exercise exclusive administrative control over the configuration,
 security,
 and management of hardware,
 software,
 and firmware that transmit or store CJI on County-managed infrastructure,
 regardless of the user department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Access and Change Governance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To maintain the integrity of the County network,
 specific decision rights are reserved exclusively for Information Operations leadership:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access Control
\series default
:
 The granting,
 modification,
 and revocation of logical access privileges to County information systems and physical access to IT-controlled facilities (e.g.,
 data centers,
 server rooms,
 network closets) shall fall under the operational authority of the IT Director,
 implemented in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Access Control Policy) and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Personnel Security and Background Screening Policy).
 For systems processing CJI,
 access decisions shall further comply with CJIS Security Policy and applicable Management Control Agreements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Change Control
\series default
:
 Changes affecting cross-departmental services,
 core infrastructure,
 or security baselines must be reviewed and approved by the IT Director and processed in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Change Management Policy).
 Significant changes affecting County-wide operations may require County Manager notification or approval in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Interdepartmental Dependencies and Obligations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Effective governance requires strict coordination between control functions.
 The following dependencies are mandatory:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Services
\series default
 (HR):
 HR serves as the authoritative source for personnel status.
 HR shall provide notification to IT—
through the designated HR information system or service desk process—
regarding onboarding,
 termination,
 or role changes to ensure secure access control (See 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fiscal Affairs
\series default
:
 Fiscal Affairs governs financial processing for technology purchases.
 Fiscal Affairs shall collaborate with IT to ensure all technology procurement aligns with the governance standards defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.10"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and supply chain risk criteria in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 and shall reject non-compliant requisitions.
\end_layout

